The paper discusses a method for symbolic regression using genetic programming, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method is designed to handle large-scale problems with a large number of variables, which suggests it may be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) or data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses a new technique for probing separability, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
